**Disclaimer:** As folks have mentioned in the comments, this is a **dangerous hack**. It is likely to have unintended side effects unless you are *certain* of the constraints on the input. If replacing `9090` on a line containing `Port` within 8 lines of a line containing `AdmServer` is exactly what you want to do, then something like this could work:

```sed
sed &quot;/AdmServer/,+8 {/Port/s/9090/$AdmServerPort/}&quot; PoolServer.xml
```

Use the `-i` flag if you want to modify the file in place.

Example input:

```xml
&lt;AdmServer&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/AdmServer&gt;
```

Example output:

```xml
&lt;AdmServer&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Foo&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/AdmServer&gt;
```

**libxml solution:**
You could pass a new `Port` attribute value as a parameter to xsltproc to use in an identity transform stylesheet:
```
xsltproc --stringparam new_port 9595 PoolServer.xsl PoolServer.xml
```

PoolServer.xsl:
```xml
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot;?&gt;
&lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot;&gt;
	&lt;!-- define $new_port as a parameter received from the shell --&gt;
	&lt;xsl:param name=&quot;new_port&quot;/&gt;

	&lt;!-- match AdmServer/Argument &#39;Value&#39; attributes
         whose sibling &#39;Name&#39; attributes are &#39;Port&#39; --&gt;
	&lt;xsl:template match=&quot;AdmServer/Argument/@Value[../@Name = &#39;Port&#39;]&quot;&gt;
		&lt;xsl:attribute name=&quot;Value&quot;&gt;
			&lt;xsl:value-of select=&quot;$new_port&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/xsl:attribute&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:template&gt;

    &lt;!-- recursively copy the rest of the xml document --&gt;
    &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;@*|node()&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
            &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;@*|node()&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
    &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
&lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;
```

Input PoolServer.xml:
```xml
&lt;AdmServer&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Sample1&quot; Value=&quot;1234&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Sample2&quot; Value=&quot;1234&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9090&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/AdmServer&gt;
```
Output:
```xml
&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot;?&gt;
&lt;AdmServer&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Sample1&quot; Value=&quot;1234&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Sample2&quot; Value=&quot;1234&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;Argument Name=&quot;Port&quot; Value=&quot;9595&quot;/&gt;
&lt;/AdmServer&gt;
```

